<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 10:31PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Alamance, southern
Orange, north central Lee, northeastern Chatham and southwestern
Durham Counties through 1115 PM EDT...
At 1031 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Burlington to 9 miles southeast of Graham to
near Carrboro. Movement was south at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Durham, Chapel Hill, Burlington, Graham, Pittsboro, Siler City,
Carrboro, Mebane, Haw River and Swepsonville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
